This paper is about deep learning and the convergence of backpropagation in deep architectures. The paper discusses the interplay between network structure and gradient convergence, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of denoising and dropout, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the statistical attributes of input data, which is a topic that falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
